# My Pokedex by Jublia AI Stack Rules

- Use **standalone components** only. Do not add new NgModules.
- Prefer **Ionic components** (`ion-*`) over custom HTML for UI primitives.
- **Read official docs before UI changes** — see `docs/development-guidelines.md` and `.cursor/rules/official-docs.mdc`.
- Keep styling aligned with design tokens in `src/theme/design-tokens.scss` and Ionic theme in `src/theme/variables.scss`.
- Use **Angular signals** for component-local reactive state.
- All PokéAPI access must go through `src/app/core/services/*`.
- Shared UI belongs in `src/app/shared/components/*`.
- Feature screens belong in `src/app/features/*` with one folder per screen.
- Use `@ionic/angular/standalone` imports, not the legacy module barrel.
- Style Ionic components via **documented APIs and CSS variables**, not ad-hoc global overrides.

## Examples

```typescript
// BAD - direct HTTP in a page
this.http.get('https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon/1')

// GOOD - service abstraction
this.pokemonService.getPokemonDetail(1)
```

```html
<!-- BAD -->
<div class="custom-button">Retry</div>

<!-- GOOD -->
<ion-button color="primary">Retry</ion-button>
```
